### DMT  
According to a transcript of his episode with Andrew Gallimore (#2403) the guest explains that during a DMT experience the brain appears to move from the ordinary waking world model → a more disordered state → then collapses into a new type of order, i.e. constructing “an entirely different model of reality”.
---

### Richard Feynman
Physicist Richard Feynman once marveled that quantum electrodynamics (QED) predicts the magnetic moment of the electron with such precision that it’s “like measuring the distance between New York and Los Angeles to within the width of a human hair.” QED’s predictions agree with experiment to better than one part in a hundred million, the most precise alignment between theory and measurement in all of science. This astonishing harmony exemplifies what Eugene Wigner called “the unreasonable effectiveness of mathematics in the natural sciences.” Such perfection seems far beyond coincidence — as if the universe itself were written in an elegant mathematical language. Whether one names this hidden order God, Nature, or pure mathematics, it suggests, as Wigner implied, that reality and mind share a common structure, and that through mathematics, humanity briefly glimpses the architecture of creation itself.
